<div id="review_3953384647" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3953384647" />
    <a title="Carolien" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7323402-carolien"><img alt="Carolien" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1386793078p2/7323402.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3953384647?book_show_action=true">Apr 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carolien" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carolien" href="/user/show/7323402-carolien">Carolien</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7323402-carolien?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7323402-carolien?shelf=african-reads-2021">african-reads-2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7323402-carolien?shelf=african-fiction">african-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3953384647" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7196639678519967092">It took me a while to get used to the pace and tone of this novel which is written completely in the first person. Khaled is an Algerian painter living in exile in Paris. He had fought in the Algerian independence war and lost an arm in combat. Now 25 years later the daughter of his former commanding officer walks into an art gallery and he falls in love with her. She is never named and he recounts their love story which ends with her wedding to another man in Constantine. Constantine is one of </span>
  <span id="freeText7196639678519967092" style="display:none">It took me a while to get used to the pace and tone of this novel which is written completely in the first person. Khaled is an Algerian painter living in exile in Paris. He had fought in the Algerian independence war and lost an arm in combat. Now 25 years later the daughter of his former commanding officer walks into an art gallery and he falls in love with her. She is never named and he recounts their love story which ends with her wedding to another man in Constantine. Constantine is one of the world's oldest cities, built around a massive gorge and therefore the bridges which the narrator uses to reflect on his life as an exile. A new author to me and I am planning on reading the remainder of the trilogy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7196639678519967092" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


