<div id="review_1655728771" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1655728771" />
    <a title="Calzean" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26416859-calzean"><img alt="Calzean" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1469230411p2/26416859.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1655728771?book_show_action=true">Jun 01, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Calzean" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Calzean" href="/user/show/26416859-calzean">Calzean</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26416859-calzean?shelf=woman-author">woman-author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26416859-calzean?shelf=culture-france">culture-france</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26416859-calzean?shelf=culture-algeria">culture-algeria</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26416859-calzean?shelf=author-algeria">author-algeria</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1655728771" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4014121476324881072">The writing is very poetic and the reflections on Algeria and Constantine over a 50 year period is fascinating. His portrait of modern Algeria where daughters are given in arranged marriages to corrupt officials because there is no other choices is particularly sad. Also sad is the general disillusionment of Arabs and what has happened after their so-called freedom.<br/>Khaled is a former fighter in the Algerian war of liberation. He lives in Paris where he has become a famous painter. He loves his m</span>
  <span id="freeText4014121476324881072" style="display:none">The writing is very poetic and the reflections on Algeria and Constantine over a 50 year period is fascinating. His portrait of modern Algeria where daughters are given in arranged marriages to corrupt officials because there is no other choices is particularly sad. Also sad is the general disillusionment of Arabs and what has happened after their so-called freedom.<br />Khaled is a former fighter in the Algerian war of liberation. He lives in Paris where he has become a famous painter. He loves his memories of his old country and when he meets the daughter of his old revolutionary commander he is consumed with passion for her. <br />This book then goes on and on about his feelings, his love and hope for a future with her. It just needed a bit more balance between the portrait of Algeria and the portrait of love lost.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4014121476324881072" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


