<div id="review_4256346241" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4256346241" />
    <a title="Bookreaderljh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1632972-bookreaderljh"><img alt="Bookreaderljh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1349050268p2/1632972.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4256346241?book_show_action=true">Sep 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bookreaderljh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bookreaderljh" href="/user/show/1632972-bookreaderljh">Bookreaderljh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789774247347" href="/book/show/426499.Memory_in_the_Flesh">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1632972-bookreaderljh?shelf=books-read-in-2021">books-read-in-2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4256346241" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15563563548069860063">The writing in this book is good but not sure about the translation. The story revolves around the painter Khaled and his obsession with the daughter of his long ago commander in a revolution where he lost an arm. The young woman is compared to his paintings - to the city of Constantine - to his daughter that wasn&apos;t - to his mother. All very erudite musings but I found them to be self-centered and the mix of politics, sex and religion (the whole point of the book) was very, very, very slow readi</span>
  <span id="freeText15563563548069860063" style="display:none">The writing in this book is good but not sure about the translation. The story revolves around the painter Khaled and his obsession with the daughter of his long ago commander in a revolution where he lost an arm. The young woman is compared to his paintings - to the city of Constantine - to his daughter that wasn't - to his mother. All very erudite musings but I found them to be self-centered and the mix of politics, sex and religion (the whole point of the book) was very, very, very slow reading. The author writes prose like poetry in a lot of ways which allowed for at least a little bit of understanding of the writing style. Seeing this entire book through the dispirited lens of Khaled was just not something I appreciated. Also lost track of a number of salient philosophical discussions as the constant CONSTANT use of the interrogative in the writing started to drive me crazy. Found I was counting question marks rather than paying attention to the themes. There was also some "Ick" factor considering how much Khaled obsesses over this young woman whom he has known since she was an infant. Her story could have been interesting - growing up without a father who is idolized by society - a sheltered education away from her homeland - her teasing of both Khaled and a poet Ziad without giving herself to either - her own writings - and ultimately an arranged marriage for the good of her uncle (not her). Just could never like Khaled and his naval gazing so the book not for me. May not be true for everyone - but I knew too little about the culture of Algiers and the Middle East revolutions to appreciate the back story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15563563548069860063" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


