        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4120739531" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16019744519446210868">“Painters, they are the craziest creative type of all. Their insanity is extreme, sudden and scary. I am interested in the line between creativity and insanity: the moment that out of the blue they declare that they have transcended and rejected logic. They act out of defiance and leave us overawed with the canvas of their life.”<br/><br/>The Bridges of Constantine (a Novel by Ahlem Mosteghanemi):- Ahlem Mosteghanemi apparently is the best selling female author in the Arab world. The Arabic original of th</span>
  <span id="freeText16019744519446210868" style="display:none">“Painters, they are the craziest creative type of all. Their insanity is extreme, sudden and scary. I am interested in the line between creativity and insanity: the moment that out of the blue they declare that they have transcended and rejected logic. They act out of defiance and leave us overawed with the canvas of their life.”<br /><br />The Bridges of Constantine (a Novel by Ahlem Mosteghanemi):- Ahlem Mosteghanemi apparently is the best selling female author in the Arab world. The Arabic original of this title was awarded the 1998 Naguib Mahfouz Medal for Literature.<br /><br />Bridges of Constantine is the story of Khaled, a wounded former revolutionary in the Algerian war of liberation, currently self-exiled in Paris, after becoming disillusioned with the corruption and the state of affairs of his newly independent country. Now a celebrated painter (“a painter who isn’t a photographer chasing reality, someone who doesn’t paint with the eye, but with memory, imagination...and other things”), Khaled is confronted with a strange contradiction as he is “living in a country that respected his talents but rejected his wounds and belonged to a nation that respected his wounds but rejected him. Which one to choose when he was the person and the wound at the same time?”<br /><br />Bridges of Constantine Is also the story of Hayat, daughter of Khaled’s old revolutionary commander, who is now an upcoming young novelist (she firmly believes that “we write novels to kill the people whose existence has become a burden to us. We write to get rid of them”).<br /><br />Bridges of Constantine is a good read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16019744519446210868" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


