    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3871790313" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3871790313" />
    <a title="George P." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5975123-george-p"><img alt="George P." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1602041237p2/5975123.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3871790313?book_show_action=true">May 02, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="George P." class="user" itemprop="url" name="George P." href="/user/show/5975123-george-p">George P.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5975123-george-p?shelf=author-not-us-canada-or-uk">author-not-us-canada-or-uk</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5975123-george-p?shelf=set-in-africa-or-asia">set-in-africa-or-asia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5975123-george-p?shelf=2021-country-challenge">2021-country-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3871790313" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2820520274816214462"><b> 2.5*</b><br/>I have read novels by Moroccan and Egyptian writers, but this was my first by an Algerian writer. The style is a mixture of traditional novel and prose poetry. I found the style to be excessively melodramatic to the point of histrionic, but I wanted to get more variety in my reading and stuck with it. Evidently Mosteghanemi is very popular in Arabic- speaking countries, I would guess mostly with women readers. The story could be described as revolving around a failed romance, which became f</span>
  <span id="freeText2820520274816214462" style="display:none"><b> 2.5*</b><br />I have read novels by Moroccan and Egyptian writers, but this was my first by an Algerian writer. The style is a mixture of traditional novel and prose poetry. I found the style to be excessively melodramatic to the point of histrionic, but I wanted to get more variety in my reading and stuck with it. Evidently Mosteghanemi is very popular in Arabic- speaking countries, I would guess mostly with women readers. The story could be described as revolving around a failed romance, which became fairly one-sided, along with a focus on violent death and injury in revolution or uprising. Frequently the writing is choppy short poetic sentences. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2820520274816214462" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

